om: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">D</span>elivery completed within the deadline: 27<sup style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">th</sup>&nbsp;November 2017.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">F</span>inal lab test (Post sample) result received: 24<sup style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">th</sup>&nbsp;December 2017</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1.3em; margin-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">(Shelter tool kit &amp; Blanket were purchased under framework agreement from Kuala Lumpur</span>)</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1.3em; margin-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">Challenges for CGI Sheet Distribution:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.3em;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Inspection procedure (lab testing) took longer time than expected.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">BDRCS faced challenges to store CGI sheets in the district branch as well as in the communities.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Due to different mode of transportation delivery to distribution points took longer time then estimated.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">People those who got CGI sheet and shelter support want to have cash money too, to repair their houses.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1.3em; margin-top: 0px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1.3em; margin-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">BDRCS Hotline:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.3em;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Beneficiaries and others people can give opinion, suggestions or complaint by using the newly opened (Effective from December 6, 2017) hotline number:&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">+880 1811 458524</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>', NULL, '2021-03-30 07:28:32', '2021-03-30 07:28:32'),
(14, 17, NULL, 'RCY Co-Curriculum Activity', '2015-03-09', '2021-03-30', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1617089669.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-family: \'-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, sans-serif\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">In order to accelerate Red Crescent Youth activities, the Ministry of Education of the Government of Bangladesh has introduced Red Crescent Youth movement in all the educational institute as co-curriculum activity since 2009. As part of this RCY Co-curriculum activity, the educational institutes (grade VI &ndash; XII) from a 53-member team to conduct youth activities. The Y&amp;V Department undertakes measures for the capacity building of RCY volunteers and members and organizes basic training on RCRC Introduction, First Aid and arrange earthquake and fire drill with the support of Civil Defense authority. These RCY teams are also engaged in institution base social activities such as gardening, cleaning and literature competition. Under Co-curriculum activity BDRCS reached approximately 13,800 educational institutes and formed RCY teams in each institute. All of these institutes RCY members received training on RCRC Induction and FA training. Among these many institute organized earthquake and fire drill with the active support of local unit RCY volunteers. Last year BDRCS organized Trainer Training for 271 RCY volunteers of 68 units. These volunteers nowadays playing active role to organize training RCY members in 68 units.</span></p>', NULL, '2021-03-30 07:34:29', '2021-03-30 10:25:23'),
(15, 14, NULL, 'EcoSec CHT Project', '2021-03-09', '2021-03-30', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1617089740.jpg', '<section id=\"section_1780644665\" class=\"section\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; display: flex; padding: 30px; position: relative; min-height: auto; width: 1140px; flex-flow: row; align-items: center; font-family: \'-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, sans-serif\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\r\n<div class=\"section-content relative\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; width: 1080px; z-index: 1; position: relative !important;\">\r\n<div id=\"row-380281976\" class=\"row\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; width: auto; margin-left: -15px; margin-right: -15px; max-width: 1170px; display: flex; flex-flow: row wrap; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">\r\n<div class=\"col medium-6 small-12 large-6\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 15px 30px; width: 555px; max-width: 50%; flex-basis: 50%;\">\r\n<div class=\"col-inner\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: auto; width: 525px; background-position: 50% 50%; background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; flex: 1 0 auto;\">\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1.3em; margin-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">Economic Security (EcoSec) CHT Project:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1.3em; margin-top: 0px; text-align: justify;\">The EcoSec project under CD Department is being implemented since October 2014 in partnership with the International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC). The people of Chottogram Hill Tracts (CHT) are highly vulnerable to food security due to their limited access and unavailability of food. ICRC Dhaka delegation identified the humanitarian needs of the affected population where EcoSec interventions either directly or indirectly can contribute to minimize the human suffering in the context of&nbsp;Chottogram&nbsp;Hill Tracts and EcoSec Project was introduced in CHT with the partnership of BDRCS in the year of 2014 for that purpose.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<section id=\"section_2008119751\" class=\"section\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; display: flex; padding: 30px; position: relative; min-height: auto; width: 1140px; flex-flow: row; align-items: center; font-family: \'-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, sans-serif\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\r\n<div class=\"bg section-bg fill bg-fill bg-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; overflow: hidden; width: 1140px; position: absolute; inset: 0px; height: 722px; padding: 0px !important; margin: 0px !important; background-position: 50% 50%; background-size: cover !important; background-repeat: no-repeat !important; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 1s ease 0s;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"section-content relative\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; width: 1080px; z-index: 1; position: relative !important;\">\r\n<div id=\"row-13330354\" class=\"row\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; width: auto; margin-left: -15px; margin-right: -15px; max-width: 1170px; display: flex; flex-flow: row wrap; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">\r\n<div class=\"col small-12 large-12\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 15px 30px; width: 1110px; max-width: 100%; flex-basis: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"col-inner\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; margin-left: auto; margin-right: 0px; width: 1080px; background-position: 50% 50%; background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; flex: 1 0 auto;\">\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1.3em; margin-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">Key Components</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1.3em; margin-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">A. Livelihood outcome at household (HH) level:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.3em;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Food consumption</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Food production</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Income support</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Basic living conditions and</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1.3em; margin-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">B. Policy, institution and processes (PIPs) level:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.3em;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Local capacity in terms of access to institutions and services.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1.3em; margin-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">Achievements:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.3em;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Project is being implemented in 03 districts (Bandarban, Khagrachari and Rangamati) with the households of number 3179 (Bandarban-1357, Khagrachari-1162, Rangamati-660) up to August 2018.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Training on livestock has been provided.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Homestead gardening and agriculture training has been provided.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">99% of total beneficiaries have ensured three-time meals/day utilizing cash grants of BDT 30,000 in cultivation.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">They became free by repaying loans from their earning and their children are becoming able to receive education from schools.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 1.3em;\">Their earning has reduced their wants and crises mostly.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>', NULL, '2021-03-30 07:35:40', '2021-03-30 07:35:40'),
